{"title_page": "Choti Zareen", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{More citations needed|date=July 2010}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = \n| settlement_type                 = Town and union council\n| other_name                      = '''\u0686\u0648\u0679\u06cc \u0632\u06cc\u0631\u06cc\u06ba'''\n| image_skyline                   = \n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_map                       = \n| pushpin_map                     = \n| pushpin_label_position          = \n| pushpin_mapsize                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Pakistan\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Pakistan]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Subdivisions of Pakistan|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Districts of Pakistan|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Dera Ghazi Khan District]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[Tehsils of Dera Ghazi Khan|Kot Chutta]]\n| subdivision_name3               = \n| subdivision_type4               = \n| subdivision_name4               = \n| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = [[Union councils of Pakistan|Union council]]\n| leader_title                    = [[Member of the National Assembly of Pakistan|MNA]]\n| leader_name                     = Muhammad Khan Leghari\n| leader_title1                   = [[Member of Provincial Assembly|MPA]]\n| leader_name1                    = [[Awais Leghari]]\n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| area_metro_km2                  = \n| population_as_of                = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = \n| population_density_km2          = \n| population_urban                = \n| population_density_urban_km2    = \n| coordinates                     = {{coord|29|50|41|N|70|29|32|E|display=inline}}\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 114\n| elevation_ft                    = 374\n| timezone                        = [[Pakistan Standard Time|PST]]\n| utc_offset                      = +5\n| timezone_DST                    = \n| utc_offset_DST                  = \n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Code]]\n| postal_code                     = 32200\n| area_code                       = 064\n| blank_name                      = \u0686\u0648\u0679\u06cc \u0632\u06cc\u0631\u06cc\u06ba\n| blank_info                      = \n| website                         = choti haan dii boti\n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = Choti Zareen\n}}\n'''Choti Zareen''' (Urdu: '''\u0686\u0648\u0679\u06cc''' '''\u0632\u06cc\u0631\u06cc\u06ba''') is a town and [[union councils of Pakistan|union council]] of [[Dera Ghazi Khan District]], Tehsil [[Kot Chutta]] in the [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]] province of [[Pakistan]].<ref>\n[http://www.nrb.gov.pk/lg_election/union.asp?district=7&dn=D.G.%20Khan Tehsils & Unions in the District of D.G. Khan - Government of Pakistan] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120209041130/http://www.nrb.gov.pk/lg_election/union.asp?district=7&dn=D.G.%20Khan |date=February 9, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nIt is 30&nbsp;km to the southwest of [[Dera Ghazi Khan]] and 26 km to the east of [[Sulaiman Mountains|Sulaiman Range]].\nThere are linked families like Chandia, leghari, Gulyani, Babbar, bhutta, sayyad etc \nIt is the ancestral town of the Alyani tribe and chandia tribe.\nIt is home town of [[Farooq Leghari|Sardar Farooq Ahmad Khan Leghari]] and his family. Villages surrounding the town are mostly inhabited by [[Buzdar (tribe)|Buzdar]],kaleri Birmani,Chandia tribe, Kachhela, Ramdani, Dadoani, Changwani,Jogiani,Hasnani,Ahmadan Nangri and other tribes,\nlike Jaffar Family from drugh musa khail.[{\u03b2alochistan}] come in choti named mullan jaffar pathan.\n\n== History ==\nThe town contains some historical buildings with unknown history (Tomb of Mir Rindo Khan).[[File:Photos-of-Dera-Ghazi-Khan-Tomb-of-Mir-Rindo-Khan-at-Choti-Zareen-DG-Khan-DG-Khan-Images-Pics.jpg|thumb|Tomb of Mir Rindo  Khan]]\n\n== Demography ==\nChoti Zareen is further divided by Chak system.\n\n* Chak Bakhar\n* Chak Buzdar\n* Chak Dodhara\n* Chak Chandia\n* Chak Jaluhar\n* Chak Kama\n* Chak Talpur\n* Chehal Chahan\n* Thatha Gabbolan\n* Mutfariq Chahan\n* Nawan Janobi\n* Nawan Shumali\n\n== Agriculture ==\n[[Agriculture]] is the main occupation of the people. Land is very fertile and is irrigated by Dera Ghazi Khan Canal originating from [[Taunsa Barrage]] on [[Indus River]]. Seasonal torrents (locally known as '''\u0646\u0626\u06cc\u06ba \u06cc\u0627 \u0644\u06c1\u0691''') from [[Sulaiman Mountains]] are also the source of irrigation. Main crops cultivated in [[Choti Zareen]] are wheat, cotton and rice. Vegetables and fruits are also cultivated at small level.\nAt some areas Tobacco is cultivated. The topography of the town is slope of koh sulaiman range with much salanity (saline sodic soil)\n\n== Politics ==\nThe town has produced politicians of all ranks from President to Federal and Provincial Ministers. Politically area has been governed by [[Leghari tribe|Leghari Tribe]]. [[Buzdar (tribe)|Buzdar, kachhela, Talpur, Ahmadani, Jogiani, Hasnani,Mulan jaffar pathan,  tribe]] are their counterpart in politics. The main political figures of Choti Zareen are\n\n# [[Farooq Leghari|Farooq Ahmad Khan Leghari]] (Former President of Pakistan).\n# Maqsood Khan Leghari.\n# [[Jamal Leghari|Jamal Khan Leghari]] (Chief of Leghari tribe).\n# [[Awais Leghari|Awais Ahmad Khan Leghari]] (Former Federal Minister for Power).\n# Muhammad Khan Leghari (MNA).\n# Doctor Saeed Buzdar\n# Mirza khan Talpur\n# Afzal khan Hasnani\n# Ghulam Abbas khan Jogiani \n# Manzoor Ahmed khan changwani.\n# Alwaz hussain Jaffar pathan\n# Chief Nouman Bilal pathan\n# Goda Sadiq khan jaffer pathan\n# Sardar Hafiz Abad Ullah Leghari\n# Sardar Qasim Khan Leghari\n\n== Languages ==\n[[Saraiki language|Saraiki]] and [[Balochi language|Balochi]] are the main languages spoken in Choti Zareen.\n\n== Education ==\n[[Choti Zareen]] is considered amongst the backward areas of Punjab. The main reason behind is that there are very few educational institutions in this areas.\n\n=== Schools and colleges ===\n* Government Boys High School Choti Zareen\n* Government Girls High School Choti Zareen\n* Government girls degree college\n* Government boys college\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*{{cite book |last=Horst |first=Kristen Nehemiah |date=2011 |title=Ahmedani |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PER4tgAACAAJ&dq=Ahmedani+book&hl=en&redir_esc=y |location= |publisher=Dign Press |page=112 |isbn=978-613-6-66572-6}}\n\n{{Dera-Ghazi-Khan-Union-Councils}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Dera Ghazi Khan District]]\n[[Category:Union councils of Dera Ghazi Khan District]]\n\n{{DeraGhaziKhan-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{More citations needed|date=July 2010}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = \n| settlement_type                 = Town and union council\n| other_name                      = '''\u0686\u0648\u0679\u06cc \u0632\u06cc\u0631\u06cc\u06ba'''\n| image_skyline                   = \n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| image_map                       = \n| pushpin_map                     = \n| pushpin_label_position          = \n| pushpin_mapsize                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Pakistan\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Pakistan]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Subdivisions of Pakistan|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| subdivision_